# Artifacts and Archiving

##    Jenkins Pipeline - Archive Artifacts
you will learn how to **save build artifacs for future user**.

pipeline {
    agent any
    environment {
        INSTITUTE_NAME = "Pathnex"
    }
    Stages {
        stages('Checkout') {
            steps {
                git url: 'https://gthub.com/Pathnex/sample-java-app.git'
            }
        }
        satge('Build') {
            steps {
                sh  'mvn clean package'
            }
        }
        Stage('Archive') {
            steps {
                archiveArtifacts artifacts: 'target/*jar', fingerprint: true
            }
        }
    }
}

##    GitLab CI - Artifacts
you will learn how to **store artifacts in GitLab CI**.

Stages:
 - build

build:
  stage: buil
  image: mven:3.8.1-jdk-17
  script:
    - git clone https://github.com/pathnex/sample-java-app.git
    - cd sample-java-app
    - mvn clean package
  artifacts:
    paths:
      - target/*,jar
    expire_in: 1 week 
